<HEADLINE>
<P>
JERRY GOLDEN; MOBILE HOME INDUSTRY PIONEER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jerry Golden, 75, former chairman of Golden West Homes, a mobile home building 
firm he founded in 1965. 
</P>
<P>
Golden began in the industry in 1940, when the mobile home business was in its 
infancy, and worked in the Midwest before starting his manufacturing firm in 
Santa Ana. He sold his interest in the firm in 1983 to the William Lyon Co. and 
retired. His philanthropies included the City of Hope which named him Industry 
Man of the Year in 1972. In Newport Beach on Feb. 5 of heart failure. 
</P>
</TEXT>
