<HEADLINE>
<P>
UNA HANBURY; WIDELY EXHIBITED SCULPTOR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Una Hanbury, 86, a sculptor whose work is found at the National Portrait 
Gallery and other museums and galleries around the world. 
</P>
<P>
Miss Hanbury's works, in bronze, cast aluminum, stone, terra cotta and marble, 
are in more than 500 private and public collections worldwide, including those 
of the Portrait Gallery, the Smithsonian Institution, the John F. Kennedy 
Center for the Performing Arts, all in Washington, and the Royal Academy in 
London. Her monumental bronze sculptures and portraits include those of 
scientist Robert Oppenheimer and artist Georgia O'Keeffe. She became a fixture 
in the Santa Fe, N.M., arts community after moving there 25 years ago. In Santa 
Fe on Feb. 9. 
</P>
</TEXT>
