<HEADLINE>
<P>
BUSH, GORBACHEV 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In the past few days your paper has displayed dramatically the tide of history 
that is engulfing the world today. On the same day that Mikhail Gorbachev 
finally triumphed over Article 6 of the Soviet constitution, effectively 
abolishing the most wicked system of tyranny in this century, George Bush 
donned the front page defending our grossly bloated defense budget (Part A, 
Feb. 7). There could hardly be a more vivid example of how one superpower 
leader has risen to the challenge and is riding the crest of history, while the 
other is intent on being swept away with the past. 
</P>
<P>
J. DAVID MILES 
</P>
<P>
Beverly Hills 
</P>
</TEXT>
