<HEADLINE>
<P>
4 DEAD, 1 MISSING IN BLAST AT MOTEL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
HAGERSTOWN, Md. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An explosion and fire, apparently caused by a gas leak, ripped through a 
three-story motel Sunday morning and killed at least four people. 
</P>
<P>
Some guests escaped by jumping out of windows, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
At least 10 people were injured and one woman was missing and feared trapped in 
the rubble. Officials said that at the time of the blast, utility crews were on 
the way to the motel to deal with a reported leak from a natural gas line. 
</P>
<P>
The blast blew out the front of the 62-unit Super 8 Motel and hurled debris as 
far as 300 feet, Fire Chief Gary Hawbaker said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, Amid the RubbleA natural gas leak apparently triggered an explosion and 
fire that ripped through a three-story motel in Hagerstown, Md., killing at 
least four people. At least 10 other people were injured and one was missing. 
United Press International; Photo, (Southland Edition) Still SmolderingA 
natural gas leak apparently triggered an explosion and fire that ripped through 
a three-story motel in Hagerstown, Md., killing at least four people. At least 
10 other peoplewere injured and one woman was unaccounted for and believed to 
be trapped in the rubble. 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
