<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: 1 KILLED, 1 HURT WHEN CAR HITS PARKED TRUCK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
One person was killed and another seriously injured Sunday morning when their 
speeding car smashed into a parked flatbed truck on rain-slick Sepulveda 
Boulevard in Sherman Oaks, police said. 
</P>
<P>
The driver, who police said appeared to have been drinking, was arrested on 
suspicion of manslaughter. 
</P>
<P>
Theodore Glennon, 27, of Long Beach was free on $5,000 bail Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
Glennon told police he and two friends were heading north on Sepulveda near 
Valley Heart Drive at 3:05 a.m. when his car was cut off by another car. He 
said he applied his brakes and swerved into the truck, which was loaded with 
3,000 pounds of rubbish, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Police said Glennon was speeding at the time of the collision, but they had not 
determined how fast he was going. 
</P>
<P>
One passenger was pronounced dead at the scene. The other was taken to 
Northridge Hospital Medical Center, where he was in critical condition. 
</P>
<P>
The two passengers were not identified Sunday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
