<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: DRIVERS HURT WHEN RTD BUS HITS CAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two people were injured Sunday morning when a Rapid Transit District bus 
collided with a car in Northridge, police said. 
</P>
<P>
The car driven by Michelle Chon, 25, of Northridge was heading south on Reseda 
Boulevard about 7:20 a.m. when it apparently ran a red light, police said. 
</P>
<P>
It was hit by an RTD bus heading east on Parthenia Street that was driven by 
Laura Allen, 29, of Los Angeles. There were no passengers on the bus. 
</P>
<P>
The impact of the collision sent Chon's car spinning into the westbound lanes 
of Parthenia. The bus smashed into a retaining wall on the southeast corner of 
the intersection. 
</P>
<P>
Allen was admitted to Northridge Hospital Medical Center with a broken arm. 
Chon was treated for a broken clavicle and released. 
</P>
<P>
Andrea Greene, an RTD spokeswoman, said the bus was starting its morning route 
along Line 420, which runs across the San Fernando Valley along Parthenia. She 
said another bus was dispatched from the RTD depot in Chatsworth minutes after 
the accident to avoid delays. 
</P>
</TEXT>
