<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO SPORTS ET CETERA: UCSD MEN GAIN FIRST TWO TENNIS VICTORIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
After an 0-3 start against Division I teams, the UC San Diego men's tennis team 
recorded consecutive victories against Division II Cal State Bakersfield and 
Division III Cal State San Bernardino Sunday at home. UCSD defeated CSUSB, 7-2. 
</P>
<P>
A later match against Air Force was delayed by rain. It will resume Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
The Tritons swept singles competition, 6-0, had to forfeit at No. 1 doubles, 
then split the remaining two doubles matches. Winning in the top three singles 
positions were Francois Monnar, Chris Belloli and Steve Stukovsky. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
RUGBY 
</P>
<P>
Defending tournament champion Old Mission Beach Athletic Club lost to Belmont 
Shore, 18-15, in the championship game of the OMBAC tournament at Robb Field in 
Ocean Beach. 
</P>
<P>
That was the second time OMBAC lost to Belmont Shore this season. 
</P>
<P>
Cal State Long Beach defeated Cal Poly San Luis Obispo, 33-3, in the college 
division. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
CYCLING 
</P>
<P>
UC Santa Barbara edged San Diego State in team scoring at the SDSU Classic over 
the weekend. In Sunday's Criterium, Trevor Thorpe of UCSB won the mens' A race 
(50 laps, 30 miles) and SDSU's Bob Noones took second. SDSU's Stephanie Lucero 
won the womens' A race (29 laps, 20 miles). 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
BADMINTON 
</P>
<P>
Asok Boopathy defeated Tom Reidy, 5-15, 15-10, 15-13, in the mens' A singles 
finals of the Dave Freeman Open at Balboa Park. Liz Aronohn defeated Denise 
Jones, 11-2, 11-5, in the womens' A singles. All four players are members of 
the Arizona State badminton team. 
</P>
