<P>
India to Ground Airbuses: India will ground its fleet of new A320 airbuses 
while experts study the airworthiness of the planes following the crash of an 
Indian Airlines airbus last week in which 90 people died. Civil Aviation 
Minister Mohammad Arif Khan said technical snags had since been reported with 
other airbuses among the remaining 14 so far delivered to India's domestic 
carrier by the four-nation West European consortium Airbus Industrie. Khan said 
Indian Airlines would suspend further airbus deliveries pending the outcome of 
a preliminary inquiry into the crash. 
