<P>
Business; Part D; Page 2; Column 1; Financial Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
99 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Service Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Creative Artists Agency Invests in Bank: A partnership affiliated with 
Hollywood talent firm Creative Artists Agency paid $3.2 million to buy 287,615 
shares of stock in National Mercantile Bancorp in Century City as part of a 
sale of stock by the lender. 
</P>
<P>
The stock purchases give the agency nearly 10% of the bank. In addition, 
various clients and partnerships affiliated with Breslauer, Jacobson, Rutman 
&amp; Sherman, a business management firm, paid $2.9 million for 261,330 
shares. National Mercantile plans to sell another 105,555 shares to other 
entertainment-related investors. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
CREATIVE ARTISTS AGENCY; NATIONAL MERCANTILE BANCORP; INVESTMENTS; 
PARTNERSHIPS; AGENTS 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
