<HEADLINE>
<P>
YUGOSLAVIANS EDGE NEWPORT IN WATER POLO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Club Partizan, Yugoslavia's top water polo club team, defeated Newport, 8-7, on 
Sunday at Newport Harbor High School in the first match of a two-week training 
tour on the West Coast. 
</P>
<P>
Partizan, a team coached by Yugoslavian Olympic Coach Ratko Rudic, took an 8-5 
lead on Dusan Popovic's goal with 5 minutes 45 seconds remaining. 
</P>
<P>
Newport's Mike Evans, a former UC Irvine player, then scored his team-high 
third goal of the match with 4:59 remaining. George Newland scored a minute and 
a half later, cutting Partizan's lead to 8-7. 
</P>
<P>
Chris Duplanty, goalkeeper for UC Irvine's 1989 NCAA championship team, had 
seven saves for Newport. Aleksandar Sostar had 10 saves for Partizan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
