<HEADLINE>
<P>
PAIRINGS FOR OCC, FULLERTON, TOP-SEEDED GOLDEN WEST SET 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVE KRESAL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
HUNTINGTON BEACH 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Golden West is the top-seeded team in the women's Southern California community 
college basketball playoffs, it was announced Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
Orange Coast and Fullerton join Orange Empire Conference champion Golden West 
in the 16-team field. 
</P>
<P>
Golden West (32-1) plays host to 16th-seeded Antelope Valley (16-10) in the 
first round at 7:30 p.m. Wednesday. OCC (26-5), the sixth-seeded team, plays 
host to No. 11 Ventura (23-8) and No. 12 Fullerton (16-13) plays at 
fifth-seeded College of the Canyons (22-6). 
</P>
<P>
The winners advance to the regional finals that will be played either Friday or 
Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
The final four meet in the state tournament March 1-3 at College of the 
Sequoias in Visalia. 
</P>
<P>
Pairings for the men's tournament will be announced on Tuesday. STEVE KRESAL 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
